<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 1: MOUNTING ENGINE ON STAND - MOUNTING
        ENGINE
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>MOUNTING ENGINE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="mount" graphiccount="2">
            <title>Mount the Engine</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Cap
                    <emph type="bold">ALL</emph>openings to prevent debris from entering.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>WHENEVER MOUNTING AN ENGINE TO A REPAIR STAND, REFER TO THE INSTRUCTIONS INCLUDED WITH THE
                            MOUNTING STAND AND ITS CORRESPONDING ADAPTER PLATES FOR SPECIFIC DIRECTIONS ON THEIR SAFE
                            USE. USE ONLY METRIC M-10/GRADE 8 BOLTS WHEN MOUNTING THE ENGINE TO AN ENGINE STAND.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install recommended adapter plate
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE 4151</emph>
                    as directed. Refer to instructions included with engine stand
                    <emph type="bold">OEM4137</emph>
                    and secure adapter plate to side of engine (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600111">1.11</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Adapter plate must be mounted to engine first before installing engine stand. Locating
                            guide pins (made locally) are recommended to assist in aligning and holding adapter plate.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>CAUTION SHOULD BE USED WHEN HOISTING THE ENGINE TO THE STAND TO AVOID DAMAGE TO VALVE
                            COVER/INTAKE MANIFOLD. USE A SAFETY CATCH ON THE HOIST HOOK WHEN LIFTING THE ENGINE BY THE
                            LIFTING EYES.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Attach engine stand to adapter plate (
                    <emph type="bold">Figure
                        <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600112">1.12</hotlnk>
                    </emph>
                    ).
                </para>
                <figure id="ef1600111" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5044" filename="../figeg5/EG5044.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.11 Attach Adapter Plate</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600112" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5047" filename="../figeg5/EG5047.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1"
                             scalefitwidth="248px"/>
                    <caption>Figure 1.12 Attach Engine Stand To Adapter Plate</caption>
                </figure>
            </step1>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
